This paper discusses a privacy-preserving system for data analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of "sticky noise" to protect privacy also involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and the potential vulnerabilities in the system relate to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and information theory (cs.SI).
